01:36.348 --> 01:37.432
Where?

01:38.434 --> 01:40.351
I want a haircut.

01:41.103 --> 01:43.104
The president's in town.

01:43.314 --> 01:44.522
We don't care.

01:45.149 --> 01:47.692
We need a haircut.
We need to go across town.

01:48.277 --> 01:52.030
We'll hit traffic that
speaks in quarter inches.

01:52.406 --> 01:55.200
Just so I know...

01:55.284 --> 01:57.452
...which president
are we talking about?

01:57.453 --> 01:59.704
United States.

01:59.830 --> 02:01.581
Barriers will be setup.

02:02.249 --> 02:04.626
Entire streets deleted
from the map.

02:06.378 --> 02:08.378
Show me my car.

02:14.303 --> 02:15.470
What have we learned then?

02:15.679 --> 02:18.139
Our system is secure.
We're impenetrable.

02:18.474 --> 02:19.933
There's no rogue program.

02:20.226 --> 02:21.768
It would seem, however...

02:21.769 --> 02:24.312
- Eric!
- No, we ran every test.

02:25.231 --> 02:28.399
No one's overloading the
system or manipulating our sites.

02:28.400 --> 02:29.692
When do we do all this?

02:29.693 --> 02:30.485
Yesterday.

02:30.486 --> 02:32.820
At the complex, our rapid response team.

02:33.072 --> 02:35.490
There is no vulnerable point of entry.

02:35.491 --> 02:37.909
Our insurer did a threat analysis.

02:38.160 --> 02:39.577
We are buffered from attack.

02:39.578 --> 02:40.286
Everywhere.

02:40.412 --> 02:41.120
Yes.

02:41.413 --> 02:42.705
Including the car?

02:43.374 --> 02:45.083
Including, absolutely, yes.

02:45.084 --> 02:46.292
My car, this car...

02:46.293 --> 02:48.378
Eric, yes! Please...

02:50.798 --> 02:55.009
We've been together, you and I,
since the little-bitty startup.

02:55.177 --> 02:59.013
I want you to tell me that
you still have the stamina to do this job.

02:59.431 --> 03:00.390
Single mindedness.

03:00.391 --> 03:02.475
This car, your car...

03:02.476 --> 03:04.561
The relentless will.

03:05.521 --> 03:07.438
'cause I keep hearing
about our legend

03:07.439 --> 03:10.775
that we were young, 
smart and raised by wolves

03:10.776 --> 03:12.861
that the phenomena of reputation

03:12.862 --> 03:16.239
is a delicate thing.
Person rises on a word

03:16.240 --> 03:18.867
and falls on a syllable.

03:20.494 --> 03:21.995
I know I'm asking the wrong man.

03:21.996 --> 03:23.079
Oh, what?

03:23.706 --> 03:26.541
Where's the car last night
after we ran our tests?

03:26.750 --> 03:28.459
I...

03:29.044 --> 03:31.629
I don't know.

03:35.259 --> 03:37.468
Where do all these limos go at night?

03:38.012 --> 03:39.971
I know I'm changing the subject.

03:39.972 --> 03:41.472
Haven't been sleeping much.

03:41.473 --> 03:43.558
I look at books and drink brandy.

03:43.559 --> 03:48.479
What happens to all these stretched
limousines that prowl the throbbing city all day long?

03:48.480 --> 03:50.231
Where do they spend the night?

03:57.698 --> 04:02.076
Do you ever get the feeling, sometimes,
that you don't know what's going on?

04:04.330 --> 04:06.915
Do I wanna ask you what you mean by that?

04:06.916 --> 04:09.501
All this optimism

04:09.585 --> 04:11.669
All this booming and soaring.

04:11.670 --> 04:16.716
Things happen like...
bang! This! And that! Simultaneous.

04:16.716 --> 04:19.844
I put out my hand
and what do I feel?

04:21.180 --> 04:25.058
I know there are a thousand things
that you analyze every 10 minutes

04:25.059 --> 04:30.438
patterns, ratio, indexes,
whole maps of information.

04:31.607 --> 04:33.358
I love information.

04:34.485 --> 04:36.903
Eric, this is our
sweetness and light.

04:36.904 --> 04:39.364
It is a fuckall wonder

04:39.365 --> 04:41.866
and we have meaning
in this world

04:42.743 --> 04:47.831
people eat and sleep in
the shadow of what we do.

04:49.124 --> 04:50.959
But at the same time

04:50.960 --> 04:53.044
What?

04:57.424 --> 05:01.553
Any special reason we're in
the car instead of the office?

05:01.554 --> 05:03.638
What makes you think we're
in the car instead of the office?

05:03.806 --> 05:05.515
If I answer that question...

05:05.599 --> 05:06.641
Based on what premise?

05:06.642 --> 05:11.521
I know I'll say something
that's half-way clever, but...also shallow

05:11.522 --> 05:14.357
and probably inaccurate on some level

05:14.358 --> 05:17.902
and then you will pity me
for having been born.

05:17.903 --> 05:19.988
We're in the car 'cause
I need a haircut.

05:19.989 --> 05:22.490
Get the barber come to the
office, get a haircut there

05:22.491 --> 05:25.243
or have the barber come
to your car, just...

05:25.244 --> 05:27.829
get your haircut and
go to the office.

05:27.997 --> 05:31.666
A haircut has what?
Associations

05:31.667 --> 05:34.210
Calendar on the wall,
mirrors everywhere.

05:34.211 --> 05:38.214
There's no barber chair here.
Nothing swivels but chair your in, Shiner.

05:58.360 --> 06:00.445
Where's your car?

06:02.072 --> 06:05.408
We can't seem to find it.

06:05.409 --> 06:07.160
I'd offer you a ride.

06:07.161 --> 06:10.246
I couldn't. Absolutely.

06:10.247 --> 06:12.332
I know you work enroute.

06:12.750 --> 06:14.751
and I like taxis.

06:14.752 --> 06:20.089
I was never good at geography and I
learned things by asking the drivers where they come from.

06:20.090 --> 06:22.759
They come from horror and despair.

06:23.511 --> 06:25.261
Yes, exactly.

06:25.971 --> 06:30.767
One learns about the country where
unrest is occurring by riding the taxis here.

06:32.561 --> 06:34.729
I haven't seen you in a while.

06:38.275 --> 06:40.818
I looked for you this morning.

06:42.738 --> 06:44.280
Your eyes are blue.

06:45.324 --> 06:47.158
Have you eat breakfast yet?

06:47.910 --> 06:49.244
No.

06:51.080 --> 06:54.249
Good. I'm hungry for
something thick and chewy.

06:55.584 --> 06:58.002
You never told me you were blue eyed.

06:59.129 --> 07:01.130
When are we going to talk about?

07:02.633 --> 07:04.634
I want a heliboard on the roof.

07:05.177 --> 07:08.388
I've acquired the air rights,
but we still need the zoning variants.

07:08.389 --> 07:09.806
Don't you wanna eat?

07:10.474 --> 07:13.017
There's a shooting range
next to the elevator bank.

07:14.687 --> 07:16.354
Let's talk about us.

07:16.689 --> 07:18.022
You and I?

07:18.274 --> 07:20.441
We're here so we might as well.

07:21.610 --> 07:23.027
When are we going
to have sex again?

07:24.989 --> 07:27.156
We will, I promise.

07:28.534 --> 07:30.368
We haven't in a while now.

07:31.579 --> 07:33.788
When I work, you see...

07:34.039 --> 07:36.207
the energy is precious.

07:36.208 --> 07:38.293
When you write?

07:38.294 --> 07:40.378
Yes.

07:41.714 --> 07:43.256
Where do you do this?

07:43.591 --> 07:45.341
I look for you, Elise.

07:45.968 --> 07:47.886
I curl up somewhere.

07:48.220 --> 07:50.513
I've always done this.

07:50.639 --> 07:53.141
My mother used to send
people to find me

07:53.434 --> 07:57.061
maids and gardeners,
combing the house and rounds

07:57.563 --> 08:00.273
She thought I was
dissolvable in water.

08:00.983 --> 08:03.276
I like your mother.

08:03.986 --> 08:05.987
You have your mother's breasts.

08:06.322 --> 08:08.072
Breasts?

08:10.326 --> 08:12.660
Great stand-up tits.

08:15.039 --> 08:17.624
Tell me this: where will you go now?

08:18.334 --> 08:21.044
To a meeting somewhere
to your office?

08:21.045 --> 08:22.837
Where is your office?

08:22.838 --> 08:24.923
What do you do, exactly?

08:25.841 --> 08:28.343
You know things,
I think this is what you do.

08:29.053 --> 08:31.346
I think you're dedicated to knowing.

08:31.597 --> 08:37.268
I think you acquire information and turn it
into something stupendous and awful.

08:38.479 --> 08:41.438
You're a dangerous person.
Do you agree?

08:42.691 --> 08:44.359
A visionary.

08:55.663 --> 08:57.956
A report from the Complex.

08:57.957 --> 09:00.041
It's a credible threat,
not to be dismissed.

09:00.751 --> 09:03.002
Which means riding cross town is...

09:03.003 --> 09:05.880
Had numerous threats, all credible.

09:05.881 --> 09:07.465
I'm still standing here.

09:07.758 --> 09:10.635
Not a threat to your safety, to his.

09:11.303 --> 09:13.054
Who the fuck is "his"?

09:13.055 --> 09:16.683
The president's.
This means a ride cross town...

09:16.684 --> 09:20.353
does not happen unless we make
a day of it, with cookies and milk.

09:21.480 --> 09:25.942
Do people still shoot at presidents?
I thought there were more stimulating targets.

09:27.194 --> 09:32.198
In the next block, there are two
haircutting saloons, there's one and two.

09:32.783 --> 09:35.034
No need to go cross town

09:35.661 --> 09:38.079
Situation is unstable.

09:39.206 --> 09:40.915
Here.

09:44.420 --> 09:46.296
I know that smile, Michael.

09:46.297 --> 09:51.676
I think the yuan...I mean there's
reason to believe we may be leveraging too rashly.

09:51.677 --> 09:53.178
It's gonna turn our way.

09:53.179 --> 09:56.014
Yes, I know, it always has.

09:57.266 --> 09:59.434
The rashness you think you see.

09:59.435 --> 10:02.103
What is happening doesn't chart.

10:03.439 --> 10:05.064
It charts.

10:05.065 --> 10:11.529
You just have to search a little harder.
Don't trust standard models, think outside the limits.

10:11.947 --> 10:13.615
The yuan is making a statement.

10:13.616 --> 10:15.408
Read it and leap.

10:15.409 --> 10:18.745
We are betting big time here.

10:18.913 --> 10:23.750
I know that smile and I wanna respect it,
but the yuan can't go any higher.

10:23.751 --> 10:25.210
I wanna trust it.

10:25.336 --> 10:27.837
We're borrowing enormous enormous sums.

10:27.838 --> 10:30.757
Any assault on the borders of
perception is gonna seem rash at first...

10:30.758 --> 10:33.927
Yeah, come on, we're speculating into the void!

10:34.970 --> 10:37.263
Your mother blamed the
smile on your father

10:37.681 --> 10:39.349
he blamed her

10:39.850 --> 10:41.643
there's something deadly about it

10:42.019 --> 10:44.229
she thought she had to enroll
you in special counseling.

10:44.230 --> 10:46.564
I think we ought to adjust.

10:49.985 --> 10:51.277
Where's Shiner?

10:51.278 --> 10:53.363
On his way to the airport.

10:55.241 --> 10:57.283
Why are they called airports?

10:57.576 --> 11:01.663
I know I can't answer these questions
without losing your respect.

11:01.914 --> 11:04.207
Shiner told me our network is secure.

11:04.208 --> 11:05.500
Then it is.

11:06.669 --> 11:09.796
Safe from penetrations.

11:13.133 --> 11:16.344
Why am I seeing things that
haven't happened yet?

11:23.227 --> 11:24.686
How old are you?

11:29.441 --> 11:30.859
What? 22!

11:30.860 --> 11:32.944
You look younger.

11:33.946 --> 11:37.824
I was always younger than anyone
around me. One day I began to change.

11:38.868 --> 11:40.952
I don't feel younger.

11:41.412 --> 11:43.955
I feel located totally nowhere.

11:45.082 --> 11:48.501
Think I'm ready to quit,
basically the business.

11:48.961 --> 11:52.463
Put a stick of gum in your
mouth and try not to chew it.

11:56.051 --> 12:01.139
For someone your age and your gifts, there's only one
thing in the world worth pursuing both professionally and intellectually.

12:01.140 --> 12:03.224
What is it, Michael?

12:04.518 --> 12:07.228
The interaction between
technology and capital

12:07.229 --> 12:09.314
the inseparability.

12:09.648 --> 12:12.358
Highschool was the last true challenge.

12:14.069 --> 12:18.323
There's a poem I read in which
a rat becomes the unit of currency.

12:18.824 --> 12:21.618
Yes, that would be interesting.

12:21.619 --> 12:23.453
Yeah, that would
impact the world economy.

12:23.454 --> 12:26.372
The name alone,
better than the dong or the kwacha.

12:26.373 --> 12:27.582
The name says everything.

12:27.583 --> 12:28.374
Yes.

12:28.375 --> 12:29.334
The rat.

12:29.335 --> 12:32.128
Yes, the rat close lower
today against the euro.

12:32.129 --> 12:36.007
Yes, there's going concern that
the Russian rat will be devalued.

12:36.008 --> 12:37.759
White rats, think about that.

12:37.760 --> 12:39.052
Yes, pregnant rats.

12:39.053 --> 12:41.846
Major sell-offs of
Russian pregnant rats.

12:41.847 --> 12:43.598
Britain converts the rat.

12:43.599 --> 12:45.433
Joins trend to universal currency.

12:45.434 --> 12:47.227
Yes, US is establishing
the rat standard.

12:47.228 --> 12:50.188
Is every US dollar
redeemable for rat?

12:51.273 --> 12:53.149
Dead rats!

12:53.275 --> 12:56.027
Yes, stockpiling of dead rats called

12:56.320 --> 12:58.530
global health menace.

13:00.157 --> 13:04.869
How old are you, now that
you're not younger than everyone else?

13:43.158 --> 13:44.868
Was I expecting you?

13:45.744 --> 13:47.328
Just passing by.

13:47.621 --> 13:51.833
Thought you'd drop in, did you?
That's nice. I'm glad.

13:52.334 --> 13:54.502
Been a while.

13:58.465 --> 13:59.966
I read about it.

13:59.967 --> 14:03.845
Of course. Or did I see it on TV?

14:04.847 --> 14:05.930
What?

14:05.931 --> 14:09.058
What? The wedding!

14:09.226 --> 14:11.352
Strange you didn't tell me.

14:12.271 --> 14:13.563
It's not so strange.

14:13.564 --> 14:15.607
Not so strange?

14:15.608 --> 14:18.526
Two great fortunes!

14:18.527 --> 14:24.616
Like one of those great arranged
marriages of old empire Europe.

14:25.034 --> 14:28.578
Except I'm a world citizen with
a New York pair of balls.

14:29.538 --> 14:33.333
So how many billions together
do you two represent?

14:34.043 --> 14:35.752
She's a poet.

14:38.464 --> 14:40.715
Is that what she is?

14:41.759 --> 14:44.219
I thought she was a Shifrin.

14:44.220 --> 14:45.553
Little of both.

14:53.020 --> 14:55.647
So rich and crisp.

14:56.440 --> 14:59.817
Does she let you touch
her personal parts?

15:01.820 --> 15:04.322
You look gorgeous today.

15:04.323 --> 15:10.578
For someone who's 41 and
finally understands what her problem is.

15:10.579 --> 15:12.038
What's that?

15:12.665 --> 15:14.999
Life is...

15:16.126 --> 15:18.503
too contemporary.

15:20.589 --> 15:22.549
So how old is your consort?

15:26.262 --> 15:28.429
Nevermind, I don't wanna know.

15:30.391 --> 15:32.267
You'd tell me to shut up.

15:32.268 --> 15:34.352
Oh, one more question.

15:34.854 --> 15:36.771
Is she good in bed?

15:39.066 --> 15:41.609
Is she good in the limo?

15:41.610 --> 15:43.152
I don't know yet.

15:43.153 --> 15:46.948
Aww, that's the trouble
will old money.

15:47.449 --> 15:49.826
Now tell me to shut up.

15:52.371 --> 15:54.539
I know something you wanna know.

15:55.541 --> 15:57.083
What's that?

15:57.084 --> 16:01.629
There's a Rothko in private 
hands that I have the privileged knowledge of.

16:01.630 --> 16:03.715
It's about to become available.

16:03.716 --> 16:05.800
You've seen it?

16:07.261 --> 16:10.138
Three, four years ago, yes.

16:10.139 --> 16:12.223
It is...

16:13.726 --> 16:16.311
luminous.

16:16.312 --> 16:18.188
What about the chapel?

16:18.397 --> 16:19.898
What about it?

16:19.899 --> 16:21.733
I've been thinking about the chapel.

16:21.734 --> 16:23.568
You can't buy the god-damn chapel.

16:23.569 --> 16:24.611
How do you know?

16:24.612 --> 16:26.487
Contact the principals.

16:26.488 --> 16:29.991
I thought you'd be thrilled
about the painting. One painting.

16:29.992 --> 16:34.913
You don't have a important Rothko
and you've always want one, we've talked about this!

16:34.955 --> 16:36.998
How many paintings in this chapel?

16:38.876 --> 16:40.919
I don't know.

16:41.504 --> 16:43.004
14? 15?

16:44.131 --> 16:46.799
If they're selling the chapel,
I'll keep it intact.

16:46.800 --> 16:47.800
Tell them!

16:49.136 --> 16:51.596
Keep it intact? Where?

16:51.597 --> 16:53.681
Tell them!

16:54.433 --> 16:59.354
In my apartment there's
sufficient space.

16:59.980 --> 17:02.065
I can make more space.

17:02.066 --> 17:03.691
The people need to see it.

17:03.692 --> 17:05.068
Let them buy it.

17:05.069 --> 17:07.153
Let them outbid me.

17:07.363 --> 17:13.701
Forgive the pissed way to say this,
but the ??? chapel belongs to the world.

17:13.702 --> 17:15.787
It's mine if I buy it.

17:17.373 --> 17:18.705
How much do they want for it?

17:18.707 --> 17:22.167
They don't wanna sell the chapel

17:22.169 --> 17:30.802
and I don't wanna give you lessons in self-denial and social
responsibility because I don't believe for a second you're as cruel as you sound.

17:32.096 --> 17:33.555
How much?

17:39.728 --> 17:42.814
What does it mean to spend money?

17:43.732 --> 17:44.899
A dollar?

17:44.900 --> 17:46.985
A million?

17:46.986 --> 17:48.194
For a painting?

17:48.195 --> 17:50.280
For anything.

17:52.241 --> 17:54.784
I have two private
elevators now.

17:55.327 --> 17:58.496
One is programmed to play
Satie piano pieces.

17:58.497 --> 18:00.582
And move at one-quarter the normal speed.

18:01.292 --> 18:05.170
This is right the Satie and this is the
elevator I take when I'm in a certain...

18:05.671 --> 18:07.005
let's say...

18:07.548 --> 18:09.132
unsettled mood.

18:09.133 --> 18:11.509
It calms me, makes me whole.

18:11.927 --> 18:13.803
Who's the other elevator?

18:13.804 --> 18:15.013
Brother Fez.

18:15.014 --> 18:16.014
Who's that?

18:16.015 --> 18:18.099
The Sufi rap star.
You don't know this?

18:18.100 --> 18:20.185
I miss things.

18:20.686 --> 18:22.812
I don't know what
money is anymore.

18:23.898 --> 18:25.607
I'm losing money
by the ton today.

18:25.608 --> 18:27.442
Many millions.

18:27.443 --> 18:29.110
Betting against the yuan.

18:29.111 --> 18:30.528
Isn't the yuan asleep?

18:30.529 --> 18:32.614
Currency markets never close.

18:32.615 --> 18:37.243
Shanghai runs day and night,
all the major exchanges, seven days a week.

18:37.620 --> 18:38.703
I miss that.

18:42.082 --> 18:43.416
I ???

18:48.714 --> 18:50.548
How many millions?

18:52.092 --> 18:53.676
Hundreds of millions.

18:55.387 --> 18:56.638
How old are you?

18:58.224 --> 18:59.265
28?

19:00.434 --> 19:01.351
28.

19:02.978 --> 19:05.396
I want you to go to the chapel
and make them an offer.

19:06.315 --> 19:07.899
Whatever it takes.

19:08.651 --> 19:10.193
I want everything that's there.

19:10.194 --> 19:12.278
Walls and all.

19:15.241 --> 19:16.908
I remember what you told me once.

19:17.284 --> 19:18.076
What's that?

19:19.745 --> 19:21.830
Talent is more
erotic when it's wasted.

19:23.249 --> 19:24.457
What did I mean?

19:30.172 --> 19:31.130
A word?

19:31.465 --> 19:32.382
Yeah.

19:33.008 --> 19:35.260
Complex recommends extra security.

19:35.261 --> 19:37.404
- You're not happy about this.
- No.

19:37.405 --> 19:38.596
First, a threat
at the president.

19:38.597 --> 19:40.682
You're confident you can
handle whatever it comes up?

19:40.683 --> 19:43.935
Now an attack on the managing
director of the International Monetary Fund.

19:45.062 --> 19:45.895
Arthur Rapp?

19:45.896 --> 19:47.939
Arthur Rapp, yes.

19:47.940 --> 19:48.582
Where?

19:48.732 --> 19:51.693
Nike, North Korea, while being
interviewed on television.

19:52.486 --> 19:54.195
It's on all the channels.

19:54.738 --> 19:58.032
<i>Director Rapp, will this
change your policy on the yuan?</i>

19:58.284 --> 20:02.162
<i>The yuan is uncharacteristically
inflated, which makes it unstable</i>

20:02.163 --> 20:05.123
<i>and eventually it will drop,
and when it...</i>

20:16.218 --> 20:17.302
The Complex...

20:20.097 --> 20:22.182
accept their recommendation.

20:22.183 --> 20:24.267
Good.

20:46.373 --> 20:50.793
All these limos, my God,
that you can't tell one from another.

20:50.920 --> 20:53.004
We could be kids on prom night.

20:53.506 --> 20:55.840
Or some dumb wedding wherever.

20:56.300 --> 20:58.551
What's the charm of identical?

20:58.636 --> 21:03.681
That I'm a powerful person that
